978	    /// is returned.
979	    ///
980	    /// An operation is considered to be ready if it doesn't have to block. Note that it is ready
981	    /// even when it will simply return an error because the channel is disconnected.
982	    ///
983	    /// Note that this method might return with success spuriously, so it's a good idea to always
984	    /// double check if the operation is really ready.
985	    ///
986	    /// # Examples
987	    ///
988	    /// ```
989	    /// use crossbeam_channel::{unbounded, Select};
990	    ///
991	    /// let (s1, r1) = unbounded();
992	    /// let (s2, r2) = unbounded();
993	    ///
994	    /// s1.send(10).unwrap();
995	    /// s2.send(20).unwrap();
